column1: #: description: Parameterized vertex level efficiencies as a function of number of particles associated to a truth decay vertex
column2: and the vertex invariant mass for truth decays with $73$ mm $< R_{\mathrm{decay}} < 84$ mm. Selected particles are required to have nonzero electric charge
column4: and $d_0 > 2$ mm. The per-vertex efficiency is evaluated only for truth vertices that have at least 5 associated tracks
column6: and are in the region $4$ mm $< R_{\mathrm{decay}} < 300$ mm
column7: and $|Z_{\mathrm{decay}}| < 300$ mm. A truth vertex satisfies the vertex level efficiency if it can be matched to a reconstructed DV which passes the final vertex selection.

column1: #: keyword phrases: Proton-Proton Scattering | Supersymmetry | SUSY
